- Wait.

25:15.514 --> 25:17.080
- Is it gonna hurt?
- Not at all, okay?

25:17.124 --> 25:18.168
On three.

25:18.212 --> 25:19.996
But wait--

25:20.040 --> 25:21.084
I'm scared.

25:21.128 --> 25:23.217
Arlette,
I need help over here!

25:23.260 --> 25:25.567
Bay 24!

25:25.611 --> 25:27.917
We all get scared, but we can't
go through life with a pinky

25:27.961 --> 25:29.440
shaped like a bendy straw,
can we?

25:29.484 --> 25:30.572
- Okay.
- Okay.

25:30.616 --> 25:32.531
On three. One, two--

25:32.574 --> 25:34.663
[pinky cracks]
Brunstetter, splint!

25:34.707 --> 25:36.099
See?
Easy-peasy.

25:36.143 --> 25:37.492
Kid with LLC?

25:37.536 --> 25:39.102
All right, I need two IVs

25:39.146 --> 25:40.582
and a portable chest.
- I paged surgery.

25:40.626 --> 25:41.975
Okay, now page
every other department.

25:42.018 --> 25:43.585
Right.
Hey, how you feelin'?

25:43.629 --> 25:45.761
Yeah, I'm a little hungry. Go.

25:45.805 --> 25:48.242
[voices echoing]
[sustained ringing]

25:48.285 --> 25:49.983
[screams]

25:50.026 --> 25:54.204
[yells] What's happening to me?

25:54.248 --> 25:56.250
You're about to have a baby.

25:56.293 --> 25:58.165
Hey, can we get
some help over there?

25:58.208 --> 26:01.124
- Busy!
- [sighing]

26:01.168 --> 26:03.562
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

26:03.605 --> 26:04.998
<i>♪</i>

26:09.176 --> 26:11.047
I don't know
what you want me to tell you.

26:11.091 --> 26:13.006
The truth.

26:13.049 --> 26:15.748
How hard is that?

26:15.791 --> 26:19.012
Not the first time you've heard
that today, one suspects.

26:21.101 --> 26:24.626
Oh, man, my marriage
of 15 years is ending,

26:24.670 --> 26:27.194
and I don't think
it's that ridiculous to suggest

26:27.237 --> 26:30.284
that maybe that's
the root of my problem.

26:30.327 --> 26:32.939
Tell me about your date.

26:32.982 --> 26:34.027
Um, I did already.

26:34.070 --> 26:35.855
Not the boudoir.

26:35.898 --> 26:37.291
The date.

26:37.334 --> 26:39.075
All right, all right.

26:39.119 --> 26:41.991
So he was hot.

26:42.035 --> 26:43.471
You know, way out of my league.

26:43.514 --> 26:45.255
That's not me being
self-deprecating.

26:45.299 --> 26:46.605
That's just the facts,
all right?

26:46.648 --> 26:48.041
Objectively speaking,

26:48.084 --> 26:50.696
he was like if Apollo
walked off of Mount Olympus.

26:50.739 --> 26:54.874
You know, but our profiles
matched up on the app,

26:54.917 --> 26:57.224
and, uh,
I didn't pursue it at first,

26:57.267 --> 26:58.660
because I thought
it was too far-fetched.

26:58.704 --> 27:00.880
But then he beeped me.

27:00.923 --> 27:02.403
Is that a euphemism?

27:04.013 --> 27:05.406
Is that a what?

27:05.449 --> 27:07.364
No, he beeped--
if you like someone's profile

27:07.408 --> 27:08.714
on the app, you beep them.

27:08.757 --> 27:09.932
You p--you ping them.

27:09.976 --> 27:12.456
Do you understand
what I'm talking about?

27:12.500 --> 27:16.156
Anyway, he set it up.
He reached out,

27:16.199 --> 27:18.027
and, uh,
and then he propositioned me

27:18.071 --> 27:19.681
before we even got dessert.

27:19.725 --> 27:21.552
Essentially,
it was the easiest date

27:21.596 --> 27:22.989
of all time.
You know, all I had to do

27:23.032 --> 27:25.774
was just say yes.
- Hmm.

27:25.818 --> 27:27.733
Sounds familiar.

27:27.776 --> 27:29.299
Oh, is that your usual?

27:29.343 --> 27:31.693
Must be nice to be so popular.

27:31.737 --> 27:33.826
It's familiar,
because it's extremely

27:33.869 --> 27:37.917
reminiscent of your first date
with someone else.

27:37.960 --> 27:40.876
<i>[sentimental music]</i>

27:40.920 --> 27:44.706
<i>♪</i>

27:44.750 --> 27:46.795
Martin?

27:46.839 --> 27:49.493
Isn't that your origin myth?

27:49.537 --> 27:54.063
Staggeringly handsome Martin
swoops down on dear, sweet Iggy

27:54.107 --> 27:57.066
at the bar
and picks him right up.

27:57.110 --> 27:59.721
The location's different,
but the dynamics--

27:59.765 --> 28:02.419
exactly the same.

28:02.463 --> 28:07.120
Moments ago, you said your
marriage of 15 years is ending.

28:07.163 --> 28:11.037
Now, that is a sentence without
a subject, but this divorce

28:11.080 --> 28:12.821
didn't just happen.

28:12.865 --> 28:14.388
Your relationship is ending

28:14.431 --> 28:17.130
because someone
decided to end it.

28:17.173 --> 28:18.653
Which of you was it?

28:18.697 --> 28:20.742
<i>♪</i>

28:20.786 --> 28:22.004
Me.

28:22.048 --> 28:24.006
Damn right.

28:24.050 --> 28:26.052
You felt so strongly
it was over

28:26.095 --> 28:28.402
that you upended
your entire life,

28:28.445 --> 28:32.145
and then for your first
post-Martin intimacy,

28:32.188 --> 28:34.582
you chose a man
who replicated every part

28:34.625 --> 28:36.627
of the relationship
you just left.

28:36.671 --> 28:38.020
[sighs]

28:38.064 --> 28:41.241
Your impotence
wasn't your body failing.

28:41.284 --> 28:44.374
It was your body
giving you a warning.

28:44.418 --> 28:47.769
This is not what you want.

28:49.466 --> 28:51.294
Why did you end you marriage?

28:51.338 --> 28:55.385
<i>♪</i>

28:55.429 --> 28:57.213
Because I couldn't be
who I wanted to be.

28:57.257 --> 29:00.913
Well, marvelous news--

29:00.956 --> 29:02.784
now you can.

29:02.828 --> 29:06.048
The question is
who do you wanna be?

29:06.092 --> 29:09.095
<i>♪</i>

29:09.138 --> 29:11.445
[sighs]

29:11.488 --> 29:15.057
I was out of line,
and I apologize.

29:15.101 --> 29:16.972
Keep going.

29:17.016 --> 29:19.018
[sighs]
I have a hard time

29:19.061 --> 29:21.542
giving up control, and...

29:23.022 --> 29:24.240
I'm sorry.

29:30.464 --> 29:32.509
[sighs]
Uh...

29:33.902 --> 29:36.296
Guess who's behind the wheel
when I'm in a car.

29:37.863 --> 29:40.648
At a barbecue,
guess who's at the grill.

29:42.650 --> 29:46.480
I think it all comes down to...

29:46.523 --> 29:49.657
my dad leaving
when I was a kid.

29:49.700 --> 29:52.878
I mean, you know how it goes.
Everyone said,

29:52.921 --> 29:55.663
"You gon' be the man
of the house now."

29:57.404 --> 29:59.188
I guess I took that to heart,

29:59.232 --> 30:01.147
and, uh,

30:01.190 --> 30:02.539
I never let it go.

30:03.671 --> 30:05.412
So you didn't have a mother?

30:07.501 --> 30:10.069
Yeah, uh,
yeah, I had a mother.

30:10.112 --> 30:13.246
Was this mother not capable
of running the household?

30:16.118 --> 30:17.380
Well?

30:17.424 --> 30:18.729
Answer the woman.

30:21.341 --> 30:23.996
[sighs]
Yeah, uh, yeah.

30:24.039 --> 30:26.868
I guess she--she was capable--

30:26.912 --> 30:30.176
is--is very capable.

30:30.219 --> 30:33.092
She's a force of nature.

30:33.135 --> 30:35.964
So you're telling me that
your mother was a competent,

30:36.008 --> 30:38.358
highly intelligent woman
who knew how to do

30:38.401 --> 30:41.230
what she needed to do.

30:41.274 --> 30:44.190
<i>["Heal" by Tom Odell]</i>

30:44.233 --> 30:47.889
<i>♪</i>

30:47.933 --> 30:50.936
Okay, you know what?
Just knock me out, please,

30:50.979 --> 30:52.720
for the sake of everyone.

30:52.763 --> 30:56.463
<i>♪</i>

30:56.506 --> 31:01.424
<i>♪ Take my mind,
and take my pain ♪</i>

31:01.468 --> 31:04.079
<i>♪</i>

31:04.123 --> 31:06.734
[screams]

31:06.777 --> 31:08.518
You're doing great, Aria.
You're doing great.

31:08.562 --> 31:11.913
Baby's heart rate's dropping,
another decel.

31:11.957 --> 31:14.394
<i>♪ Heal, heal</i>

31:14.437 --> 31:16.918
Okay, the umbilical cord is
wrapped around the baby's neck.

31:16.962 --> 31:18.615
- [shrieks] What?
- Hold on, hold on,

31:18.659 --> 31:19.878
hold on, Aria.
- [crying] No, no, no!

31:19.921 --> 31:21.967
Aria, I can fix it!
Aria, Aria, Aria,

31:22.010 --> 31:24.056
you have to trust me right now, okay?

31:24.099 --> 31:25.709
I can fix it, okay?

31:25.753 --> 31:27.929
- [breathing heavily]
- Okay, okay, come on.

31:27.973 --> 31:29.235
Come on, come on, come on.

31:29.278 --> 31:30.976
[breathing heavily]

31:31.019 --> 31:32.455
[indistinct]

31:32.499 --> 31:35.981
Okay, almost got it.
Almost got it.

31:36.024 --> 31:38.244
Damn.
- [crying]

31:38.287 --> 31:39.854
What does that mean?

31:39.898 --> 31:42.335
Okay, I thought I had it,
but I can't unwrap the cord.

31:42.378 --> 31:44.641
Another decel.

31:44.685 --> 31:46.556
[voice echoing]
Fetal scalp blood pH 6.8.

31:46.600 --> 31:48.254
Okay, page OB stat.

31:48.297 --> 31:52.258
<i>♪</i>

31:52.301 --> 31:53.781
[monitor beeping]

31:53.824 --> 31:55.696
Tourniquet inflation
is effective.

31:55.739 --> 32:00.266
<i>♪ Take the heart,
take the hand ♪</i>

32:00.309 --> 32:02.703
Give me the status of
the distal edge of the TCL.

32:02.746 --> 32:07.099
<i>♪ Like an ocean takes
the dirty sand ♪</i>

32:07.142 --> 32:09.275
Thank you.

32:09.318 --> 32:10.624
For what?

32:10.667 --> 32:13.235
For changing her mind
about the procedure.

32:13.279 --> 32:16.412
Not a lot of people
can do that with Elizabeth.

32:16.456 --> 32:18.632
Uh...

32:18.675 --> 32:20.460
no, actually,
no one can do that

32:20.503 --> 32:22.549
with Elizabeth--

32:22.592 --> 32:24.290
except for you.

32:24.333 --> 32:27.075
<i>♪</i>

32:27.119 --> 32:29.512
<i>♪ Empty bottle
takes the rain ♪</i>

32:29.556 --> 32:30.949
[phone vibrates]

32:30.992 --> 32:34.300
<i>♪</i>

32:34.343 --> 32:39.131
<i>♪ Heal, heal</i>

32:39.174 --> 32:41.524
<i>♪ Help heal</i>

32:41.568 --> 32:43.657
<i>♪</i>

32:43.700 --> 32:48.096
<i>♪ And tell me
some things last ♪</i>

32:48.140 --> 32:50.794
As you can see,
there's definitely a mass,

32:50.838 --> 32:52.840
and we can't say
whether or not it's cancerous

32:52.883 --> 32:54.015
without a biopsy.

32:54.059 --> 32:55.451
Of course.

32:55.495 --> 32:57.018
So I suggest
we don't drag our heels.

32:57.062 --> 32:59.673
I'd like to get some tissue
to the pathologist today,

32:59.716 --> 33:01.153
then based on his findings...

33:01.196 --> 33:07.550
<i>♪ And tell me
some things last ♪</i>

33:07.594 --> 33:09.770
<i>♪</i>

33:09.813 --> 33:12.686
<i>♪ And tell me some</i>

33:12.729 --> 33:16.124
<i>♪ Things last</i>

33:20.563 --> 33:22.696
[screaming]

33:22.739 --> 33:24.263
Where the hell is OB?

33:24.306 --> 33:28.049
Emergency C-section on L
and D--at least an hour away.

33:28.093 --> 33:29.311
[breathing heavily]

33:29.355 --> 33:32.227
[whispering]
Okay, okay, okay, okay.

33:32.271 --> 33:34.708
[sighs]

33:34.751 --> 33:36.405
[exasperated breathing]

33:36.449 --> 33:38.016
Okay, there's the--
there's the scalp.

33:38.059 --> 33:38.929
There's the scalp.
There's the scalp.

33:38.973 --> 33:40.453
Ah!

33:40.496 --> 33:41.802
Okay, right down
from the ear,

33:41.845 --> 33:43.151
right down from the ear.

33:43.195 --> 33:45.066
Okay, there's the cord.
There's the cord.

33:45.110 --> 33:47.025
Gently over the scalp.

33:47.068 --> 33:48.896
[grunting]

33:48.939 --> 33:51.159
Come on! Come on.

33:51.203 --> 33:53.074
Okay, okay, I got it, I got it.

33:53.118 --> 33:55.033
Oh, the baby,
the baby, the baby, no!

33:55.076 --> 33:57.078
Aria, Aria, Aria,
your baby is crowning!

33:57.122 --> 33:58.297
[screaming]

33:58.340 --> 34:00.560
Okay, Aria,
I need you to look at me.

34:00.603 --> 34:02.214
Aria, Aria!

34:02.257 --> 34:04.085
Bring your focus
to your breath, okay?

34:04.129 --> 34:06.305
Okay, I got you.
I got you, I got you.

34:06.348 --> 34:07.828
Breathe with me.
Come on, Aria,

34:07.871 --> 34:09.090
that's it, that's it. Breathe.

34:09.134 --> 34:12.311
[both breathing heavily]

34:13.616 --> 34:16.576
Breathe. That's it. Breathe.

34:16.619 --> 34:19.187
[breathing calms]

34:19.231 --> 34:22.060
On the next breath,
I want you to push, okay?

34:22.103 --> 34:23.713
Okay, I need you to push.

34:23.757 --> 34:27.369
Okay, and push.

34:27.413 --> 34:29.980
[screams]

34:30.024 --> 34:31.199
Aria!

34:31.243 --> 34:33.201
Aria, your baby's
right shoulder is out.

34:33.245 --> 34:34.681
I need you to give me
one more push.

34:34.724 --> 34:36.161
Come on!
Come on, Aria!

34:36.204 --> 34:39.599
You got this!
- [grunting]

34:42.471 --> 34:45.126
[baby crying]

34:45.170 --> 34:48.564
[sighing]

34:48.608 --> 34:51.176
Okay, you did it, Aria.
You did it.

34:51.219 --> 34:54.135
[laughing]
[baby crying]

34:54.179 --> 34:57.138
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

34:57.182 --> 35:01.751
<i>♪</i>

35:01.795 --> 35:02.752
Hi.

35:02.796 --> 35:05.015
<i>♪</i>

35:05.059 --> 35:07.235
[laugh-crying]

35:07.279 --> 35:08.802
You did it, Aria.

35:08.845 --> 35:10.978
[baby crying]

35:12.110 --> 35:14.155
She's perfect.

35:14.199 --> 35:21.293
<i>♪</i>

35:36.699 --> 35:40.312
Hey.

35:43.489 --> 35:45.143
Are you new?

35:45.186 --> 35:47.014
I usually know
everybody in my O.R.

35:47.057 --> 35:49.973
It wasn't your O.R. though,
was it?

35:50.017 --> 35:52.802
[bed whirring]

35:52.846 --> 35:54.500
Hmm, <i>touché.</i>

35:56.328 --> 35:58.156
I started here last week.

35:59.331 --> 36:01.159
- How do you like it?
- Dr. Reynolds,

36:01.202 --> 36:03.161
I have worked
on four continents,

36:03.204 --> 36:05.989
in six countries
and 27 different cities,

36:06.033 --> 36:07.643
and I can say without a doubt

36:07.687 --> 36:11.125
that you are the worst patient
I've ever encountered.

36:11.169 --> 36:13.693
And Dr. Flores, she's literally
drinking in a bar right now

36:13.736 --> 36:15.434
because of you.
- [stifles laughter]

36:20.613 --> 36:22.354
Hey,
what'd you say your name was?

36:24.051 --> 36:25.270
I didn't.

36:27.881 --> 36:29.012
Hm.

36:29.056 --> 36:31.014
<i>[percussive beat]</i>

36:31.058 --> 36:33.191
<i>♪</i>

36:33.234 --> 36:34.670
Okay,
get your prescription pad.

36:34.714 --> 36:35.671
Meet me by the scales.

36:35.715 --> 36:37.238
- It's been 12 hours.
- Get it.

36:37.282 --> 36:42.678
<i>♪</i>

36:42.722 --> 36:43.810
Okay.

36:45.028 --> 36:46.204
[device beeps]

36:47.509 --> 36:49.163
- Wow.
- Told you.

36:49.207 --> 36:50.643
You actually lost a pound.

36:50.686 --> 36:52.514
No, that's not possible.
No, I--I gained at least

36:52.558 --> 36:55.387
five pounds--what?
No, that's impossible!

36:55.430 --> 36:58.694
I mean, I--I housed, like,
two orders of egg rolls.

36:58.738 --> 37:01.262
I mean, I crushed
the stuffed-crust pizza,

37:01.306 --> 37:02.829
a bear claw.
I mean, how have I not gained

37:02.872 --> 37:04.265
any weight?

37:04.309 --> 37:06.615
Wha--I raced
around all day today

37:06.659 --> 37:08.226
searching
for high-calorie food.

37:08.269 --> 37:10.140
I mean, I even skipped
a bathroom break,

37:10.184 --> 37:12.708
so I could run
across to third for poutine.

37:12.752 --> 37:15.102
There's gotta be some kind
of mistake with this thing.

37:15.145 --> 37:16.451
Well, check your phone

37:16.495 --> 37:18.061
and see how many steps
you walked.

37:18.105 --> 37:19.411
[sighs]

37:20.934 --> 37:22.936
25,201.

37:22.979 --> 37:25.286
Well, that's about 18 miles.

37:25.330 --> 37:26.809
Come back next week.

37:26.853 --> 37:29.769
[sustained ringing]

37:31.031 --> 37:34.121
[slow, labored breathing]

37:38.517 --> 37:41.607
[siren blaring in distance]

37:44.784 --> 37:46.829
Are you okay?

37:46.873 --> 37:49.484
<i>["Here Comes the River"
by Patrick Watson]</i>

37:49.528 --> 37:53.401
<i>♪ The windows
turn to fishbowls ♪</i>

37:53.445 --> 37:58.101
<i>♪ The city to seas</i>

37:58.145 --> 38:00.843
<i>♪ Cars were drowning</i>

38:00.887 --> 38:03.324
<i>♪ Underneath your feet</i>

38:03.368 --> 38:05.283
Actually, I am.

38:07.372 --> 38:10.984
You wanna try
going more than a week?

38:11.027 --> 38:14.248
<i>♪ The top of the trees</i>

38:14.292 --> 38:15.423
Yeah.

38:15.467 --> 38:16.946
<i>♪ Crowd of umbrellas</i>

38:16.990 --> 38:18.992
Yeah, I think I do.

38:19.035 --> 38:20.776
Yeah, who knows?

38:20.820 --> 38:24.127
Maybe
you don't need them anymore.

38:24.171 --> 38:26.216
<i>♪ Mary kept sewing</i>

38:26.260 --> 38:28.218
[sighs]

38:28.262 --> 38:30.743
<i>♪ Holding on to her TV</i>

38:30.786 --> 38:32.875
<i>♪</i>

38:32.919 --> 38:35.138
<i>♪ Even if the water</i>

38:35.182 --> 38:36.401
[knock at door]

38:36.444 --> 38:37.837
Waiting for a call?

38:37.880 --> 38:39.752
Uh, something like that.

38:39.795 --> 38:41.449
How can I help?

38:41.493 --> 38:44.409
Oh, yeah, uh, I just popped
by because I wanted to tell you

38:44.452 --> 38:48.456
that today was quite possibly
the most mortifying day

38:48.500 --> 38:50.676
of the last 40 years
of my life.

38:50.719 --> 38:52.504
Heard that from some
of the other department heads.

38:52.547 --> 38:54.636
Yeah, yeah, I bet you did.

38:54.680 --> 38:55.811
Yeah, I can't speak for them.

38:55.855 --> 38:57.378
I can only speak
from my experience.

38:57.422 --> 39:00.860
But, uh, your little experiment
felt embarrassing.

39:00.903 --> 39:03.515
It was humiliating.
It was painfully awkward,

39:03.558 --> 39:07.083
and I can't begin
to thank you enough.

39:07.127 --> 39:10.348
Y--sorry, really?

39:10.391 --> 39:12.132
Yeah, really.

39:12.175 --> 39:16.484
Thanks to you, I was, uh,
I was forced to look inward,

39:16.528 --> 39:19.357
and I had a breakthrough.

39:19.400 --> 39:20.880
- You did?
- I did--

39:20.923 --> 39:22.664
one that I needed more than
I could've ever have known.

39:22.708 --> 39:24.318
- There you go!
- Yeah.

39:24.362 --> 39:27.103
Now, if you'll excuse me,
I am off to have consensual sex

39:27.147 --> 39:28.366
with a stranger of my choosing.

39:28.409 --> 39:30.803
Uh, I think that's great.

39:30.846 --> 39:32.282
Heal thyself, Max.

39:32.326 --> 39:34.023
Heal thyself.

39:34.067 --> 39:35.198
[chuckles]

39:35.242 --> 39:38.245
[phone vibrating]

